	</form></div><span class="pb doctop" title="page number in print edition" id="ADMS-06-15-02-pb-0314">314<a style="padding-left: 5px" onclick="window.open('/img-document-get.xqy?image=ADMS/Pages/ADMS-06-15/ADMS-06-15-02-pb-0314.jpg', 'pageImage', 'scrollbars=1,resizable=1'); return false" onkeypress="this.onclick();" tabindex="0" title="Click to view image of page from print edition"><img src="/img-ML/page-icon.gif" width="18" height="20" style="vertical-align:middle;" alt="page icon"/></a></span><div class="doc">
        
        <h1>From C. W. F. Dumas</h1>
        <div class="docbody" xml:lang="fr">
          <div class="opener"><table class="salutationBlock">
        <tr>
		<td class="salutationLeft">Monsieur</td>
		<td class="salutationRight">Lahaie 16<span class="hi-super" style="font-size: 80%; line-height: 0.8; vertical-align: super;">e.</span> Oct. 1783</td>
	      </tr>
      </table></div>
          <p>Ma derniere du 14<span class="hi-super" style="font-size: 80%; line-height: 0.8; vertical-align: super;">e.</span> toit partie, lorsque celle de Mr. votre fils  mon Epouse nous apprit que vous avez t fort malade, &amp;, heureusement, mieux  prsent.<a class="ptr" href="#ADMS-06-15-02-0155-fn-0001" id="ADMS-06-15-02-0155-fn-0001-ptr">1</a> Nous prenons la part que nous devons &amp;  lindisposition passe, &amp;  votre convalescence, dont nous vous flicitons de grand coeur.</p>
          <p>Mrs. Matthieu Van Arp &amp; Co: mcrivent ce qui suit dAmst. 15<span class="hi-super" style="font-size: 80%; line-height: 0.8; vertical-align: super;">e</span> Oct.</p>
          <p>Le Vaisseau Amricain lElisabeth, Patron Abraham Brun, <span class="pb" title="page number in print edition" id="ADMS-06-15-02-pb-0315">[315<a style="padding-left: 0px" onclick="window.open('/img-document-get.xqy?image=ADMS/Pages/ADMS-06-15/ADMS-06-15-02-pb-0315.jpg', 'pageImage', 'scrollbars=1,resizable=1'); return false" onkeypress="this.onclick();" tabindex="0" title="Click to view image of page from print edition"><img src="/img-ML/page-icon.gif" width="18" height="20" style="vertical-align:middle;" alt="page icon"/></a>]</span>destin dici aux Indes oc[ciden]tales, a t achet par le dit Patron ici, est [encore?] sans Papiers, &amp; doit aller trafiquer en differen[tes] Places des Indes occidentales. Je vous prie de menvoyer pour ce Vaisseau un Passeport, sign par Mr. Adams, ou par vous come son Charg dAffaires. Ce Vaisseau appartient au dit Capitaine <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">seul</span> en proprit; &amp; il vous demande instamment, de faire toute la diligence possible pour lui envoyer le Passeport, &amp; aussi rponse  celle-ci par la poste de demain, avec votre promptitude connue. Au cas que vous nayez pas des Passeport de Mr. Adams, je vous prie de me le marquer dabord, &amp; de faire ensorte que je puisse, sur votre parole, assurer, que vous avez crit sur ce sujet par premiere poste  Mr. Adams: car ce Vaisseau est trs press de partir incessament.<a class="ptr" href="#ADMS-06-15-02-0155-fn-0002" id="ADMS-06-15-02-0155-fn-0002-ptr">2</a></p>
          <p>Je marque donc ce soir  Mrs. M. Van Arp &amp; Co: que je vous cris en consquence.</p>
          <p>Agrez, Monsieur, les respects de ma famille &amp; les miens, &amp; permettez que jembrasse ici Mr. votre fils. / De Votre Excellence / Le trs humble &amp; trs-obissant / serviteur,</p>
          <div class="closer"><p class="signed">C.w.f. Dumas</p></div>
          <div class="postscript">
            <p>P.S. La Garnison dUtrecht en est sortie, selon les desirs de la Bourgeoisie, avant larrive des troupes destines  la remplacer; &amp; il a fallu pour cela changer les Patentes; &amp; moi en voyant tout ce que je vois, je mcrie en stile oriental <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">O Allah! quest-ce quun Prince sans Peuple? Et que nest pas un Peuple sans Prince, ds quil le veut bien?</span><a class="ptr" href="#ADMS-06-15-02-0155-fn-0003" id="ADMS-06-15-02-0155-fn-0003-ptr">3</a></p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="translation">
          <h2><span class="hi-all-small-caps" style="font-variant: small-caps; text-transform: lowercase;">Translation</span></h2>
          <div class="opener"><table class="salutationBlock">
        <tr>
		<td class="salutationLeft">Sir</td>
		<td class="salutationRight">The Hague, 16 October 1783</td>
	      </tr>
      </table></div>
          <p>My last of the 14th had already left when that from your son to my wife apprised us that you had been seriously ill and, happily, are now better.<span class="hi-super" style="font-size: 80%; line-height: 0.8; vertical-align: super;">1</span> We are as solicitous for your past indisposition as for your convalescence, which we congratulate you on wholeheartedly.</p>
          <p>Messrs. Matheus van Arp &amp; Company wrote the following to me from Amsterdam on 15 October:</p>
          <p>The American vessel <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Elisabeth</span>, owner Abraham Brun, whose destination is the West Indies, was bought here by the abovementioned owner, is still without papers, and is to trade in various places in the West Indies. I ask you to send me a passport for this vessel, signed by Mr. Adams or by you as his charg daffaires. This vessel belongs to the aforementioned captain as the <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">sole</span> proprietor, and he asks you to immediately exercise all possible diligence to send him the passport and to respond to this by tomorrows post with your well-known promptness. In case you do not have <span class="pb" title="page number in print edition" id="ADMS-06-15-02-pb-0316">[316<a style="padding-left: 0px" onclick="window.open('/img-document-get.xqy?image=ADMS/Pages/ADMS-06-15/ADMS-06-15-02-pb-0316.jpg', 'pageImage', 'scrollbars=1,resizable=1'); return false" onkeypress="this.onclick();" tabindex="0" title="Click to view image of page from print edition"><img src="/img-ML/page-icon.gif" width="18" height="20" style="vertical-align:middle;" alt="page icon"/></a>]</span>passports from Mr. Adams, I ask you to make a note of that for me first and in such a way that I can make assurances that by your word of honor, you have written to Mr. Adams about this by the first post, since this vessel is in a great hurry to leave immediately.<span class="hi-super" style="font-size: 80%; line-height: 0.8; vertical-align: super;">2</span></p>
          <p>I am sending a note this evening to Messrs. Matheus Van Arp &amp; Company to let them know that I am writing you about this.</p>
          <p>Please accept, sir, the respects of my family and of yours truly, and permit me to send warm greetings here to your son. Your excellencys very humble and very obedient servant</p>
          <div class="closer"><p class="signed">C.w.f. Dumas</p></div>
          <div class="postscript">
            <p>P.S. The garrison at Utrecht has left, following the wishes of the burgesses, before the arrival of the troops assigned to replace them, and for that reason it was necessary to change the letters patent. And I, seeing all that I see, I express myself in the oriental style: <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Oh, Allah! What is a prince without a people? And what cannot a people do without a prince, once they desire it?</span><span class="hi-super" style="font-size: 80%; line-height: 0.8; vertical-align: super;">3</span></p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="docback">
          <div class="note-source" id="ADMS-06-15-02-0155-sn">
   <p><abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ recipients copy (A recipients copy is assumed to be in the hand of the signer unless it is otherwise described.) ]">RC</abbr> (Adams Papers); internal address: Paris  S. E. Mr. Adams Min. Pl. des E. U. Some loss of text where the seal was removed.</p>
</div>
          <div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#ADMS-06-15-02-0155-fn-0001-ptr" id="ADMS-06-15-02-0155-fn-0001">1</a>
   <p>Dumas letter of the 14th (Adams Papers) enclosed a copy of his 10 Oct. letter to Congress for <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr> to forward to America. Congress dispatch book indicates that the letter, numbered 32, reached Congress on 5 March 1784, but neither it nor five other letters dated 28 Sept. 1783, 24 Oct., 7 and 15 Nov., and 1 Dec., are in the <span class="ref-terms" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ &lt;expan&gt;Papers of the Continental Congress. Originals in the National Archives: Record Group 360. Microfilm edition in 204 reels. Usually cited in the present work from the microfilms, but according to the original series and volume numbering devised in the State Department in the early 19th century; for example, PCC, No. 93, III, i.e. the third volume of series 93.&lt;/expan&gt; ]">PCC</span> (<span class="ref-terms" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ &lt;expan&gt;Papers of the Continental Congress. Originals in the National Archives: Record Group 360. Microfilm edition in 204 reels. Usually cited in the present work from the microfilms, but according to the original series and volume numbering devised in the State Department in the early 19th century; for example, PCC, No. 93, III, i.e. the third volume of series 93.&lt;/expan&gt; ]">PCC</span>, No. 185, III, f. 95). <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Quincy Adams (17671848), son of John and Abigail Adams ]">JQA</abbr>s letter to Marie Dumas has not been found.</p>
</div>
          
          <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#ADMS-06-15-02-0155-fn-0002-ptr" id="ADMS-06-15-02-0155-fn-0002">2</a>
   <p>There is no indication that <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr> did anything regarding the letter from Van Arp &amp; Company on behalf of the <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Elisabeth</span>, and nothing further is known of the vessel.</p>
</div>
          
          <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#ADMS-06-15-02-0155-fn-0003-ptr" id="ADMS-06-15-02-0155-fn-0003">3</a>
   <p>The events at Utrecht are indicative of the rise of the Free Corps, Patriot military units independent of the stadholder. It was part of the Patriot Revolt and evidence of the growing ascendency of the Patriots over the Orangist forces of William V that would end with the 1787 expulsion of the stadholder and his subsequent restoration when Prussian forces occupied the Netherlands (<span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Simon Schama, &lt;i&gt;Patriots and Liberators: Revolution in the Netherlands 17801813&lt;/i&gt;, New York, 1977. ]">Schama, <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Patriots and Liberators</span></span>, p. 8088, 103106, 131132). For accounts of the events at Utrecht, see the <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Gazette dAmsterdam</span>, 3, 10, 14, and 17 October. Dumas appeal to Allah touches directly on this conflict between William V and the people (i.e., Patriots).</p>
</div>
          
        </div>
